From 105e13fac783726a402895ecbb17b30a71b3d346 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ramasamy Kaliappan <rkaliapp@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 3 Nov 2025 10:42:10 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:hostapd: Fix legacy station roaming across
 partner links

The legacy station connected to the link1 of  3-link AP MLD.
In the current design, when the AP receives auth/assoc request with
the same authorized STA mac address to connect with partner link2,
re-add station on the link2 during authendication.
This process deletes the station from link1 and adds it to link2 in
driver without validating whether the association request is from the
genuine client or an attacker.

Add fix during auth request from a new link with same mac address,
AP add STA mac in sta_hash table in new link bss without adding in kernel
and send auth response to the peer mac address. 
During assoc request with new link, AP trigger SA query to authorized STA and
sends assoc response with temp rejection with comeback time to the peer mac address
if no SA query response from authorized station, remove authorized STA
and when receive next assoc request, add station to the kernel and allow
to connect with new link.

Patch-dependency: r25-hostapd-Add-support-slo-sta-reconnect-with-partner-l.patch

Signed-off-by: Ramasamy Kaliappan <rkaliapp@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 src/ap/ieee802_11.c | 3 +--
 src/ap/sta_info.c   | 3 ++-
 2 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/src/ap/ieee802_11.c
+++ b/src/ap/ieee802_11.c
@@ -4386,8 +4386,7 @@ static bool check_sa_query_partner_link(
 	struct hostapd_data *bss;
 	struct sta_info *lsta;
 
-	if (sta->mld_info.mld_sta &&
-	    sta->unadded_sta &&
+	if (sta->unadded_sta &&
 	    (sta->flags & WLAN_STA_AUTH)) {
 		for_each_mld_link(bss, hapd) {
 			if (bss == hapd)
--- a/src/ap/sta_info.c
+++ b/src/ap/sta_info.c
@@ -320,7 +320,7 @@ int ap_sta_check_link_sta(struct hostapd
 	struct hostapd_data *bss;
 	struct sta_info *lsta;
 
-	if (sta && !sta->mld_info.mld_sta)
+	if (!hostapd_is_mld_ap(hapd))
 		return 0;
 
 	for_each_mld_link(bss, hapd) {
